array.note: x[i][j] is the region (number) where the square at row i and column j belongs (borders are inserted for simplicity)
y[i][j] is the value of the square at row i and column j
d[i][j] is the distance of the square at row i and column j wrt the starting square of the (same) region
s[k] is the size of the kth region

instantiation.note: setting starting squares of pre-assigned regions

group.note: setting values according to the size of the regions
controlling the size of each region

block.note: two regions of the same size cannot have neighbouring squares
